{
  "local_port": 48646,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What do Flipkart's delivery guys look for when I exchange my old phone for a new one?",
  "response": "When you exchange your old phone for a new one through Flipkart, their delivery personnel will typically check the following aspects of your old device:\n\n1. **Physical Condition**: They will inspect the phone for any physical damage, such as cracks, dents, or scratches on the screen or body. The phone should be in working condition without significant cosmetic damage.\n\n2. **Functionality**: They will test the phone to ensure that all its functions are working properly. This includes checking the display, touchscreen responsiveness, buttons, speakers, microphone, and cameras. They may also check if the phone can boot up and operate normally.\n\n3. **Battery Health**: The battery should be in good condition, and they might check its health to ensure it's not excessively degraded.\n\n4. **IMEI Verification**: They will verify the IMEI number of the phone to ensure it matches the one provided during the exchange process. This is to prevent fraud and ensure the phone is not reported as lost or stolen.\n\n5. **Software and Data**: The phone should be free of any personal data. It's recommended to perform a factory reset before handing it over. They might check if the software is functioning correctly.\n\n6. **Accessories**: Depending on the exchange offer, you might need to provide the charger and other accessories that came with the phone. Make sure to check the specific requirements of the exchange offer.\n\n7. **Model and Variant**: They will confirm that the model and variant of the phone match what was specified during the exchange process.\n\nIf your old phone meets these criteria, the exchange should proceed smoothly. It's always a good idea to review Flipkart's specific terms and conditions for the exchange program to ensure you meet all the requirements.",
